    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="101" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d101">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Harvey</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 157.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 2d ultimo, No. 301,
                            has been received. I thank you for the information it conveys relative
                            to the affair at Bahia, and commend the vigilance and diligence
                            practiced by you on this as on other occasions affecting the interests
                            of your government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
